  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Best 3-Letter Scrabble Words — Tiny Words, Big Points","description":"Master the highest-scoring 3-letter words in Scrabble including ZAX, ZEP, JAW, JOW, WAX, and FOX.","datePublished":"2026-06-30",
    "dateModified": "2026-06-05","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/best-3-letter-scrabble-words"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the highest-scoring 3-letter Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"ZAX scores 19 points — Z(10) + A(1) + X(8). It's a tool used for cutting roofing slates. Despite being obscure, it's perfectly valid in both SOWPODS and TWL dictionaries and is the top-scoring 3-letter word available."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is ZEP a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, ZEP is valid in SOWPODS (international dictionary) and scores 14 points from just 3 tiles. It refers to a zeppelin. It's one of the strongest 3-letter Z words available for tight board positions."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"When should I play 3-letter words instead of longer ones?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Play 3-letter words when the board is crowded, when you want to dump a high-value tile on a premium square, or when you can score big with parallel plays. ZAX on a TLS scores 39 points — better than many 7-letter words without bonuses."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 pt-4 pb-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">High-Scoring Words</span>
      </nav>
      <BlogCrossLinks title="Best 3 Letter Scrabble Words" />
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Best 3-Letter Scrabble Words — Tiny Words, Big Points</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔍</span> Solver</a> <a href="/activities/#quiz" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎯</span> Quiz</a> <a href="/activities/#anagram" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔀</span> Anagram</a> <a href="/activities/#rack" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎲</span> Rack</a> <a href="/activities/#wotd" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">📖</span> WOTD</a> <a href="/sixty-seconds/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">⏱️</span> 60s</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Three-letter words are the secret weapons of Scrabble. They fit in the tightest spaces, create parallel plays, and when they contain Z, X, or J tiles, they punch far above their weight. These six words score 13-19 points from just three tiles — that's tournament-level efficiency.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">19</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Top Score (ZAX)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">6.3</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Avg Pts/Tile (ZAX)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">6</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Words Featured</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">85</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Combined Points</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The Top 3-Letter Scorers</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Champion</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">ZAX</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">19 points · Z(10) + A(1) + X(8) · Slate-cutting tool</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The Z and X together deliver 18 of the 19 points. On a Triple Letter Score for either Z or X, this tiny word explodes to 29-27 points. On a Double Word Score: 38 points from three tiles.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 ZEP</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 points · Z(10) + E(1) + P(3) · Zeppelin</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 JAW</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 points · J(8) + A(1) + W(4) · Common word</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ JOW</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 points · J(8) + O(1) + W(4) · To toll a bell</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ WAX</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 points · W(4) + A(1) + X(8) · Everyday word</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10 sm:col-span-2"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">💎 FOX</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 points · F(4) + O(1) + X(8) · Easy to remember</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">When to Deploy 3-Letter Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Crowded boards:</span> When no 5+ letter word fits, a well-placed ZAX or WAX on a premium square outscores longer words. Three letters always fit somewhere.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Parallel plays:</span> Place FOX parallel to an existing word and score both simultaneously. Each letter that touches a letter below/above creates a new 2-letter word — multiply your score.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Tile dumping:</span> Got a Z or X you can't use in a longer word? JAW, WAX, FOX, and ZAX let you score big while clearing high-value tiles before the endgame.</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ZAX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">19pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ZEP</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">JAW</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">JOW</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">WAX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FOX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Pro Tip</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Memorize <span class="text-white font-medium">ZAX, ZEP, JAW, JOW, WAX, FOX</span> as your "emergency six." When the board is locked down and longer words won't fit, these guaranteed 13-19 point plays keep your scoring consistent.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/best-4-letter-scrabble-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best 4-Letter Scrabble Words</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-two-letter-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Two-Letter Words in Scrabble</span></a>
